caption: So delicious that I keep coming back.

Although the inside looks like an Uber Eats restaurant complete with bottled water and plastic silverware, the food was actually surprisingly good. Only 4 stars because the ambiance is non existent but the food is great.

Absolutely amazing! Nicandra's is the perfect cozy date spot. It's BOYB, they make fresh pasta daily, and their desserts are fantastic. The service is always friendly, and I love the different combinations in their dishes.
Food is amazing, the appetizers were awesome, highly recommend the ribs, the entrees were awesome and I really enjoyed the spices. The creme Brule is to die for, so amazing. 5 stars.
The ribs we got were ahhhhmazing and set us up for disappointment with the pasta dishes that followed.
This place obviously knows how to take care of their clients. Consistently with a kind mindset. The food is reasonably priced, regularly delicious and neat.

Just tried this spot for takeout for the first time, pasta is fresh and the mushroom appetizer is ridiculous. I've been meaning to eat more Italian food in NYC but didn't think I'd find such a great spot close to home.

11.28.2020 - came back and the outdoor seating is super cozy and warm. The espresso glazed ribs are still mindnumbingly delicious and Charmaine was still awesome (and with hand sanitizer at the ready). Cannot stress how much I love this place.  The rib appetizer was delicious and the meat fell right off the bone. The cavatelli was light and balanced and the angel hair pasta had a well portioned piece of deliciously tender octopus. And Charmaine was awesome! Will be back but next time with a bottle in hand (BYOB) :)
Such a great place with some amazing food and amazing staff. Everything I've ever had here has been delicious. Its also BYOB so what they hell are you waiting for

Small, intimate space with absolutely delicious pastas! Their pasta is handmade fresh daily and you can absolutely tell. We tried their pasta with a wild boar ragu that was incredible! And both desserts on their menu were delicious. It is BYOB so highly recommend bringing along your favorite bottle of wine. They have cups and a wine opener for you to use. The waitress is so kind and wonderful too. She remembered my partner and I from the last time we came for dinner! Really wonderful little spot for great pasta!
Delicious!!

The place has a rustic like feel. Due to the sheer size of the place, even though it was crowded, we had no wait, which was great. The food was excellent. I had the bacon and cheese omelette. The amount of bacon inside was pleasantly surprising.
I use to live by this place and go all the time! Service is super fast and friendly.

I come to this special restaurant once a month because I like the special air that is outline this place. The personel is awfuly loyal and skilfull. The service is remarkablywonderfully fast. Needless to say, the food they cook is good. I came many times and I was always delighted. The cost is modest. I highly recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.

This place is ok. Ambiance is 3. Service is 5. Food is 3.5. The food isn't spectacular, but it's good. Not memorable but filling. The best part of this to me was the complimentary parmesan sauce given before the meal. It comes in a shot glass, but I could easily have eaten a soup bowl full of the stuff. I did note that the appetizers are better than the entrees, at least that's my opinion based on what I ordered. Sorry, I'm not a millennial so I didn't take pictures of the food. All I'm giving you is my personal opinion and you can feel free to disagree. Overall a 3.5 but there's no option for that. For a regular restaurant 3.5 is good. I reserve 5.0 for an exquisite memorable experience. I just didn't feel that here. Wrong setting for that.

Absolutely amazing dinners. Perfectly cooked/seasoned dishes every time we go. Freshest pasta you can get without making it yourself. Unique and flavorful sauces for each dish. Unbelievable value for how fantastic the food is. Staff is fantastic. And a shout out to Chef Taco! Your duck ragu is a revelation! I’ve been to Nicandra’s numerous times. It never ever disappoints - it’s one of those places where I always try something different despite having my favs and I am always blown away and often gain a new fav. You can’t go wrong. It’s also BYOB which really makes it a deal. It’s an absolute gem.

We ordered the following items: - polenta shrimp ragu:  creamy and rich without being too heavy;  a wonderful mixture of southern comfort foods! - pappardelle with guanciale:  the star of this dish is the pappardelle;  it's made with tiny grooves to help soak up the sauce. - linguini nero:  the pasta had an unexpectedly tasty egg and tomatoe quality that paired well with the scallions;  it's a great choice for someone who's looking for a lighter dish

Great neighborhood restaurant. Not expensive! Very friendly young owners and short, but varied and delicious menu. Their brunch is very tasty and also unique since it carries pasta dishes, which are home made. Their avocado toast with a poached egg is also excellent. They do some magic with their roast potatoes, sour cream and sage!!  Very affordable (since there are no alcoholic beverages, but it is BYOB). So two people can expect to pay around 50$+ which is awesome!  Their weekend daytime hours are weird, (I either wake up too early or too late) but that’s my fault. Will continue to go.

Want a pasta dish that's not just spaghetti with red sauce? Don't want to spend too much on pretentious restaurants? This place is perfect for you! The pasta is hand made, and everything is cooked basically in front of you. You like to support small business? It doesn't get much smaller than that. The only guy in Nicandras at the time (sorry I don't remember your name..) was our host, server and a chef! I'm waiting for you guys to get the license to serve wine/beer and for the business to pick up! Great new addition to Bushwick/Ridgewood area.

My wife and I were pleasantly surprised by this neighborhood gem. Nicandra's is definitely worth making an effort to dine at, especially if you live in the Bushwick/Ridgewood area.  Chef (Paco?) was very welcoming and treated us to foam parmesan topped with thyme and sprinkled with pepper as we ordered Pork Chop and Hanger Steak. The Pork Chop had a sweet honey taste and was served with rainbow carrots. The Hanger Steak, on top of shredded crispy potatoes, mushrooms and balsamic pickled onions, was excellent as well. Not a huge fan of duck in general, but we shared the duck ragu dish so we can sample the homemade pasta. It was very good! Oh, and I liked their chocolate dessert enough that I forgot to share it with my wife! They put a lot of care into everything they serve.  I don't think they've been opened long, so it was nice to experience Nicandra's while it's still early and accessible. My wife and I will be going again soon, especially now that they will be offering a brunch menu. It really feels like you're getting the quality of an upscale restaurant in our neighborhood.
